Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
verifyWellTap(25.10)                                      verifyWellTap(25.10)

Name
       verifyWellTap  - Generates violation markers for missing well-tap cells
       and for well-tap cells that do not meet the rule specified for the dis-
       tance between well-tap cells

Syntax
       verifyWellTap

       [-help]

       [-area <x1 y1 x2 y2>]

       [-avoidAbutment]

       [-check <string>]

       [-cell <list_of_well_tap_cells>]

       [-fromEdge]

       [-layer <layer_name>]

       [-powerDomain <powerDomainName>]

       [-report <filename>]

       [-rule <distance>]

       [-siteOffset <number_of_sites>]

       [-wellCutCell <list_of_well_cut_cells>]

       Generates violation markers for missing well-tap cells and for well-tap
       cells that do not meet the rule  specified  for  the  distance  between
       well-tap cells. Optionally, generates a well-tap violation report.

       Honors the set_well_tap_mode settings for -cell, -rule, -well_cut_cell,
       -bottom_tap_cell, and -top_tap_cell options.

       Marks  violations  in  the  area  where well-tap placement violates the
       rule, covering the shared well of abutting rows. If there is  no  abut-
       ting  row,  marks  the violation where it covers only one-half of a row
       with a violation.

       Reports the actual distance between well-tap cells, as well as the rule
       distance. If there are no well-tap cells in a  row  and  the  row  that
       abuts  it,  or  no well-tap cells between the row end and the edge of a
       block, the software generates a message.

       Does not check row areas that are covered by blocks and their halos, or
       by placement blockages.

       The software places well-tap cells with the addWellTap command. You can
       delete well-tap cells with the deleteFiller command.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each verifyWellTap parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man verifyWellTap

       -area <x1 y1 x2 y2>
              Specifies the area in which well-taps are to be verified.

       -avoidAbutment
              Checks that there is no abutted tap cell  in  the  vertical  and
              horizontal directions.

       -check <string>
              Checks the latchup rule violation for either Nwell or Pwell. The
              <string>  can  be  either power (for Nwell check) or ground (for
              Pwell check).

       -cell <list_of_well_tap_cells>
              Specifies the well-tap cells. If not specified, uses  cells  de-
              fined  as  CLASS  CORE  WELLTAP  in the Macro section of the LEF
              file.

       -fromEdge
              Checks the rule distance from the right and left  edges  of  the
              well  tap cells, instead of from the center line. Use this para-
              meter when the design has well-tap cells of different widths.

              If this parameter is not  specified,  verifyWellTap  checks  the
              rule distance from the center line of the well-tap cells.

       -layer <layer_name>
              Specifies the layer name to check the rule.

       -powerDomain <powerDomainName>
              Limits checking to the specified power domain. If you do not use
              this  parameter,  <verifyWellTap> checks the default domain with
              the designs of N3 or below nodes, and checks the  entire  design
              for the other nodes.

       -report <filename>
              Specifies the report name.

              Default: <topCellName>.welltap.rpt

       -rule <distance>
              Specifies  the  maximum distance between two well-tap cells. The
              spacing between two well-tap cells should  be  twice  the  -rule
              value  when  measured from center to center or edge to edge. The
              distance between tap and row end should be  same  as  the  -rule
              value. For example, verifyWellTap -rule 50.

       -siteOffset <number_of_sites>
              Checks  the  offset  value in number of sites that vertical taps
              need to be aware of.

              Minimum:1

              Maximum: INT_MAX

       -wellCutCell <list_of_well_cut_cells>
              Specifies the list of cells with the well cuts. Use this  option
              to flag latch-up violations due to well cut cells.

Example
       The following command displays violations due to well cut cells:

       verifyWellTap   -rule   30   -wellCutCell  {EP32_VDDI_DSWITCH_50n_NOBUF
       EP32_VDDI_DSWITCH_50n_BUF}         -cell          {EP8T32_VDDI_GNDS_CDM
       EP8T32_VDDI_VDDS_CDM}

